727000f-a.title: Queens: Jamaica Avenue - 77th Street
727000f-a.text:
Jamaica Ave., north side, between 77th and 78th Streets, whowing
the Old Lott farmhouse. Stephen Lott came from Pennsylvania and
settled at Woodhaven. His son Hendrick was born in 1761 in this farm-
house. Other Lotts born here were Stephen N, in 182O; and his son
Charles Vanderveer, in 1846. Daniel W. Eetcham and Nicholas M. Pette,
sons-in-law of the late Charles Vanderveer Lott occupied it after 1891.
Dickel Bros., builders, purchased and demolished it in December 1922.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
